A Chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Delta State, Chief Hyacinth Enuha, has expressed optimism that Nigeria will become great again under the presidency of Asiwaju Bola Tinubu. He said his confidence in Tinubu’s ability to provide the quality of leadership needed to make the country work again, was reinforced by his choice of running mate Enuha, in a statement by his Media Adviser, Nnamdi Ofonye, hailed the choice of Kashim Shettima, describing him as a man of deep courage.   Lagos Assembly denies passing Sharia law     Court rules today on Oyo deputy governor’s impeachment     Why LASUTH is helping Nigeria address shortage of…   The statement reads: “My congratulatory message is not just coming on the heels of your emergence as the running mate to Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, but for the fact that you have become a reference point to the belief that ‘loyalty and courage to a course one believes in pays’. “All through your tenure as governor of Borno State, you showed courage and fearlessness. You spoke up with energy and worked your talk as much as your powers could carry you. That was the much I knew about you then. I love men with positive guts and energy… “Today, Kashim Shettima has been announced. His hard work has paid off; his loyalty to a course he believes in has paid off and, above all, Asiwaju’s knack for identifying intelligent people to work with has positioned Shettima.”